# Classroom Animation with OpenGL

![Classroom Animation](![alt text](image.png)(![alt text](image-1.png)(![alt text](image-2.png)))) *Example screenshot (replace with your own)*

## Description
This project is a 3D classroom animation built using OpenGL and GLUT. It features a virtual classroom environment with interactive elements including a lecturer, students, a whiteboard, projector, clock, doors, and windows with curtains. The simulation demonstrates various 3D animation techniques and lighting effects.

## Features
- **Interactive Characters**:
  - Lecturer (controlled with arrow keys)
  - Student (controlled with WASD keys)
- **Classroom Elements**:
  - Whiteboard with text
  - Projector with adjustable light
  - Digital clock showing real time
  - Opening/closing door
  - Windows with curtains
- **Lighting Controls**:
  - Classroom lighting toggle
  - Projector spotlight toggle
- **Animation Effects**:
  - Lecturer arm movements
  - Automatic movement mode
  - Student exit/enter sequences
- **Camera Controls**:
  - Rotatable view
  - Zoom in/out functionality

## Controls
| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| **Arrow Keys** | Move lecturer |
| **WASD** | Move student |
| **,** and **.** | Rotate camera view |
| **G/H** | Zoom in/out |
| **C** | Toggle clock visibility |
| **P** | Toggle projector light |
| **B** | Toggle classroom lights |
| **O** | Open/close door |
| **K** | Open/close curtains |
| **Space** | Toggle automatic movement |
| **E** | Start students exiting |
| **R** | Start students entering |

## Requirements
- C++ compiler (GCC, Clang, or MSVC)
- OpenGL libraries
- GLUT (OpenGL Utility Toolkit)

## Installation
1. Ensure you have OpenGL and GLUT installed on your system
2. Clone this repository or download the source files
3. Compile the program:
   ```bash
   g++ main.cpp -o classroom -lGL -lGLU -lglut